entries.next: Can't talk, I'm busy getting ready for my next race.
entries.cantwork: I can see you asking yourself, "Is that really Ignar Ominaz, the swoop racer?" Yes indeed, that's me. I have a job for you when you're not busy.
entries.npc_reset: If I had your lack of ambition, I'd never have become a famous swoop racer. Never give up, friend! Try me again later.
entries.npc_1_1: I can see you asking yourself, "Is that really Ignar Ominaz, the swoop racer?" Yes indeed, that's me. I don't give autographs in person, but you can buy them from my HoloNet site. I'm giving you a chance to help me tune my new swoop. I ordered a custom power converter from Coronet, but the delivery agent is lost somewhere and needs safe escort here. Can you bring him?
entries.npc_2_1: Excellent! I forget the delivery agent's name, but he's a Drall, one of those little furry folks. I expect he must be a young fan eager to get into the world of swoop racing. Bring him here and give him a thrill.
entries.npc_3_1: I don't think you understand what a rare opportunity it is to work for someone famous. Many of my fans would kill for this chance. Ah well.
entries.npc_4_1: What? You never heard of me? I expect you have and just forgot. Everyone in the galaxy followed my career back in the good Old Republic days, when I vied with Sergi-X Arrogantus for the Corulag championship. I'm still in the game, and this bike will carry me to another  championship -- as soon as you bring me that courier. Will you?
entries.npc_backtowork_1: We've talked this through already. I need to get back to work, and so do you.
entries.npc_reward_1: Well! Ah, um -- I guess this little fellow isn't quite ready for the racing game just yet. Anyway. Here, here's a little something for your time. You can tell your grandchildren you got these credits from Ignar Ominaz.
entries.npc_work_1: Where's that courier? I need that power converter soon.
entries.npc_noloc_1: I'm waiting on that courier to give me his coordinates. Check back with me in a moment. Meanwhile, you might want to check out my HoloNet site, where you can buy genuine autographed souvenirs of my career.
entries.npc_failure_1: Sorry you couldn't make it to the finish line, friend. Don't forget my HoloNet site, where you can buy genuine autographed souvenirs of my career.
entries.npc_breech_1: Are you from the customer who ordered this power converter?
entries.npc_takeme_1: What kind of idiot tries to fine-tune a swoop bike in the Agrilat Swamp? The crystal growth will ruin this power converter. Bring me to this nincompoop, and I'll tell him where he's gone wrong.
entries.npc_dropoff_1: Thanks. You, Mister -- wait, let me check my order -- Mister Ominar. I mean Ominaz. If you had the brains of a kenalpa tree, you'd know -- wait. Ominaz. Any relation to that old washed-up swoop racer?
entries.player_reset_1: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.player_sorry_1: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.npc_1_2: You know, we professional swoop racers have rivalries that go way back. Why, I remember how many times Sergi-X Arrogantus used to call me a dirty -- well, anyway. My old rival Dinnik Innik is travelling here for a head-to-head race with me, just us, no publicity. He called and said he needs a guide through the swamp. Will you escort him?
entries.npc_2_2: Good! It's hard to see Dinnik Innik, 'cause he's so small, but once you find him, bring him here for the race of the century!
entries.npc_3_2: Come on! You're missing a chance to see racing history here. I'm sure you'll change your mind soon.
entries.npc_4_2: Oh, for years Dinnik and I have fought for track position like a couple of slice hounds. He's a wiry little Chadra Fan, so there's a weight advantage right there. But the old Ignar Ominaz tactical magic brings its own advantages, you know. I expect he wants one last chance to prove he's still in the game. Poor guy, I pity him. Will you bring him here?
entries.npc_backtowork_2: I've told you plenty to get you started. It's up to you from here, friend.
entries.npc_reward_2: Uh. Umm. Well. Tell you what, friend, let's pretend this never happened. Here's something for your time. And don't forget the souvenirs available on my HoloNet site.
entries.npc_work_2: Haven't you brought Dinnik Innik here yet? I'm ready to race!
entries.npc_noloc_2: I'm waiting on Dinnik Innik to send me his coordinates. Check back with me in a moment. Meanwhile, you might want to look at my HoloNet site, where you can buy genuine autographed souvenirs of my career.
entries.npc_failure_2: Where's Dinnik? No Dinnik? I was all ready to race!
entries.npc_breech_2: Did Ignar send you to guide me?
entries.npc_takeme_2: The Agrilat Swamp gives me the chills. I'm glad you're here to take me to Ignar. I hear some disease is driving all the animals crazy.
entries.npc_dropoff_2: Thanks, friend. So, Ignar! I'm not racing you today. I'm not racing you ever again. I have a holo showing how you sabotaged my swoop in our last race, and I'm reporting you to the Commission! You'll never race again, Ignar! I wanted to see the look on your face when I told you.
entries.player_reset_2: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.player_sorry_2: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_3_2: Why are you and Dinnik Innik rivals?
entries.player_reset_3: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.player_sorry_3: I'll keep working on the mission.
